(180, 1, 2, 1, 'A planned task for a project does not get completed due to an issue that appeared three days ago but did not get resolved. The project manager wants to prevent this type of situation in the future.\n  \n What should the project manager do?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The retrospective allows issues with the execution approach to be identified and discussed in a timely fashion along with ideas for improvements. Retrospectives are a primary tool to manage project knowledge and develop the team through discussions of what is working well and team-based problem solving.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 6. Project Schedule Management / 6.6 Control Schedule, p224\n  | Agile Practice Guide (2017), 5 Implementing Agile: Delivering In An Agile Environment / 5.2.1 Retrospectives, pp50-51', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
