(200, 1, 3, 1, 'Prior to preparing a monthly project status report, a project manager identifies three new risks. All of these risks could impact critical key milestones. \n  \n The project manager wants to reference additional information before presenting this new risk information.\n  \n To which sources should the project manager refer?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'The project manager must check the risk register and risk report to see if this is indeed a new risk and to see if there was action already planned around it.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 11. Project Risk Management / 11.7 Monitor Risks, pp409-411', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
