(254, 1, 3, 1, 'The project requires the development of a human resource system (HRIS) to centrally manage human resources and payroll. The project sponsor is a multinational company.\n  \n The project manager reviews historical data on the companys human resources practices and considers the regulatory framework of the project. Still, there are concerns about project risks.\n  \n What should the project manager do in response to these concerns?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The project manager must first identify the risks before you can quantify them, develop risk mitigation plans or review them.\n  \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 11. Project Risk Management / 11.2 Identify Risks, pp409-411', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
