(264, 1, 2, 1, 'A global organization sponsors a project that involves six different companies. When the project is partially complete, the project manager learns that one stakeholder is ill and needs to decrease their level of involvement.\n  \n What should the project manager do?', 1, 1, 'Simple', 'The stakeholder engagement plan is updated to reect any processes, procedures, tools, or techniques that affect the engagement of stakeholders in project decisions and execution.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 13. Project Stakeholder Management / 13.2.3 Plan Stakeholder Engagement: Outputs, p522', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
