(433, 1, 3, 1, 'A project manager is uncertain about the duration of a new product development project and consults several groups of subject matter experts (SMEs). The first group advises that development can be finished in 14 days. The second group identifies some risks that could make the duration up to 32 days. The third group proposes a new development method that can shorten the time to 8 days.\n  \n What is the estimated development duration for the new product?', 1, 1, 'Simple', 'PERT Estimate = (Optimistic + (4 X Most Likely) + Pessimistic)/6 = (8 + (4*14) + 32)/6 = 16 days\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) /PMI/7.2.2.5/244', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
