(450, 1, 3, 1, 'A project that should have been 70 percent complete by now is only 55 percent complete. The total project budget is US$210,000, and the actual cost of work performed (ACWP) is US$162,000\n  \n What is the scheduled performance index (SPI) and cost performance index (CPI) of this project?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'EV = Actual% * BAC = 0.55*$210,000 = $115,500\n PV = Plan% * BAC = 0.70*$210,000 = $147,000\n AC = $162,000 (given)\n \n SPI = EV/PV = $115,500/$147,000 = 0.79\n CPI = EV/AC = $115,500/$162,000 = 0.71\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) /PMI/7.4.2.2/263', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
