(773, 1, 3, 1, 'Manjushree is working on a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of INR 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that INR 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. Her project sponsor wants to know the likelihood of the project being able to meet the estimate at completion. Please specify which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, NULL, 'BAC=8,50,000\n EV=2,97,500\n PV=3,40,000\n AC=4,25,000\n CPI=EV/AC=0.7\n EAC=BAC/CPI=12,41,284\n TCPI=(BAC  EV)/(BAC  AC)=552500/425000=1.3', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(774, 1, 3, 1, 'Manjushree is working on a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of INR 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that INR 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. Her project sponsor wants to know the likely variance for the project based on current performance. Please specify which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, NULL, 'BAC=8,50,000\n EV=2,97,500\n PV=3,40,000\n AC=4,25,000\n CPI=EV/AC=0.7\n EAC=BAC/CPI=12,41,284\n VAC=BAC-EAC=-391284', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(775, 1, 3, 1, 'Jasmine is working in a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of INR 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that INR 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. What is the BCWP of the project?', 1, 1, NULL, 'BAC=8,50,000\n EV=2,97,500\n PV=3,40,000\n AC=4,25,000\n BCWP (Budgeted Cost of Work Performed)=EV=2,97,500', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(776, 1, 3, 1, 'Jasmine is working on a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of INR 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that INR 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. The Cost Variance for this project is INR -1,27,500. Which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, NULL, 'BAC=8,50,000\n EV=2,97,500\n PV=3,40,000\n AC=4,25,000\n CPI=EV/AC=0.7\n As the CPI is less than 1, it is over budget by 30%', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(777, 1, 3, 1, 'Jasmine is working on a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of INR 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that INR 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. The Schedule Variance for this project is INR (-) 42,500. Which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, NULL, 'BAC=8,50,000\n EV=2,97,500\n PV=3,40,000\n AC=4,25,000\n SPI=EV/PV=0.875\n As the SPI is less than 1, it is behind schedule by 12.5%', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(778, 1, 3, 1, 'Your project has a CPI of 0.59. Which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, NULL, 'CPI (Cost Performance Index) is the rate of return / rate at which the project is getting returns. \n \n CPI of 0.59 indicates only 0.59 paise is being earned', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(779, 1, 3, 1, 'Your project has an SPI of 0.59. Which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, NULL, 'SPI (Schedule Performance Index) measures the timeline percentage of project progress.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(780, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working on a project where the SPI is 0.875 and the planned value is INR 3,40,000.00. What is the schedule variance?', 1, 1, NULL, 'SPI=0.875\n PV=3,40,000\n EV=SPI*PV=2,97,500\n SV (Schedule Variance)=EV-PV =-42,500', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(781, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working on a project where the SV is INR -42,500.00, actual cost is INR 4,25,000.00 and PV is INR 3,40,000.00. What is the CV?', 1, 1, NULL, 'EV=SV+PV=297500\n CV=EV-AC=-127500', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(782, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working on a project where the SV is INR -42,500.00, CV is INR -1,27,500.00 and PV is INR 3,40,000.00. What is the Actual Cost?', 1, 1, NULL, 'SV=EV-PV\n EV=SV+PV=2,97,500\n AC=CV+EV=425000', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(783, 1, 3, 1, 'Phyla has been asked to calculate the CPI of the project. Which tool should be BEST for her?', 1, 1, NULL, 'EVM is the right tool to used to compute CPI. Forecasting will give EAC & TCPI, but not CPI', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(784, 1, 3, 1, 'Phyla is monitoring the status of the project to update the project budget and managing changes to cost baseline. Which process is she in?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Tracking & monitoring project budget is done in controlling process', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(785, 1, 3, 1, 'Tools and techniques for performance reporting include all of the following EXCEPT:', 1, 1, NULL, 'EXCEPT is the keyword. Decision Tree Analysis (DTA) is a decision making tool rather than a performance reporting tool.\n \n All other options are performance reporting tools', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(786, 1, 3, 1, 'Which formula you should use to calculate TCPI if you want to find out the likelihood of the project being able to meet the budget at completion?', 1, 1, NULL, 'The question states \"to meet BAC\" & not \"to meet EAC\". Hence option-1 is the right answer', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(787, 1, 3, 1, 'Nick is working on a project in an organization which manufactures laptops. His company has introduced a new range of light weight laptops. In this laptop the mother board is configured and built by an external vendor. Nick as a project manager checks all the work in order to see if the vendors are performing their part of work properly or not. What can be BEST described as to what he is doing?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Nick is reviewing the performance of the motherboard configuration. \n \n Nick is not reporting the performance, but reviewing the performance.\n \n He is not reviewing the contract terms & conditions either', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(788, 1, 3, 1, 'Nick is working on a project in an organization which manufactures laptops. His company has introduced a new range of light weight laptops. In this laptop the motherboard is configured and built by an external vendor. The sponsor of the project asks Nick to let him know what is the status of the motherboard configuration. Nick had no information about it and had to wait for the vendor\'s response which came after 3 hours and then only he could update the sponsor. Nick realizes that he needs a better way to manage information about how the vendor is performing. Which of the following do you think could have helped Nick?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Records management system provides the real-time or up to date status of the deliverables or procurement items\n \n The vendor is not claiming anything here, so Claims Admin & Payment System are not the right choices', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(789, 1, 3, 1, 'Nick is working on a project in an organization which manufactures laptops. His company has introduced a new range of light weight laptops. In this laptop the mother board is configured and built by an external vendor. The sponsor of the project asks Nick to let him know what is the status of the motherboard configuration? Nick had no information about it and had to wait for the vendor\'s response which came after 3 hours and then only he could update the sponsor. Nick realizes that he needs to make sure that the vendor is delivering the quality they promised. Which of the following do you think could have helped Nick?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Nick has to do a procurement audit to ensure that the procured deliverables are as per the terms & conditions outlined in the contract. These quality of deliverables, on-time delivery, invoicing, incentives/penalties, etc.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(790, 1, 3, 1, 'Nick is working on a project in an organization which manufactures laptops. His company has introduced a new range of light weight laptops. In this laptop the mother board is configured and built by an external vendor. The vendor has also delivered the first batch of the required materials. Nick\'s company has accordingly paid the vendor for the first batch. After couple of days Nick receives an email from the Accounts Department that due to an Accounting Software error, the vendor has been paid twice as 2 invoices were generated for the same batch of work. Which of the following do you think could have helped Nick?', 1, 1, NULL, 'All vendor payouts are tracked by the Payment System.\n \n Question is specifically about payments, hence other option do not hold good.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(791, 1, 3, 1, 'Nick is working on a project in an organization which manufactures laptops. His company has introduced a new range of light weight laptops. In this laptop the mother board is configured and built by an external vendor. The vendor has also delivered the first batch of the required material. Nick\'s company has accordingly paid the vendor for the first batch. The next batch is supposed to be delivered within 2 weeks from now, however the seller says that they are supposed to deliver the same within 4 weeks. It raises disputes between the 2 parties. Which of the following do you think could have helped Nick?', 1, 1, NULL, 'As there is a dispute between buyer & seller over contract terms, Arbitration is the right option from which as amicable resolution can be expected. Both the conflicting parties will abide by the arbitration decision', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(792, 1, 3, 1, 'Nick is working on a project in an organization which manufactures laptops. His company has introduced a new range of light weight laptops. In this laptop the mother board is configured and built by an external vendor. The vendor has also delivered the first batch of the required materials. Nick\'s company has accordingly paid the vendor for the first batch. The next batch is supposed to be delivered within 2 weeks from now. Everything is going fine, however, the sponsor is not happy with Nick and his team as he has no updates about what is happening in the project. Which of the following do you think could have helped Nick?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Nick & his team do not have proper control or governance over the project. They are not pro-actively tracking project progress.\n \n If they had done proper performance reporting, then the situation would have been better', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(793, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following is NOT a part of Control Procurements?', 1, 1, NULL, 'NOT is the keyword. \n \n Procurement audits are done during contract administration & not during controlling procurements', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(794, 1, 3, 1, 'Jasmine records all transactions and maintains the Record Management System during the Control Procurement Process. Which of the following is NOT required to be recorded?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Negotiation process & formalities are finalized & baselined during contract signature/contract awarding. It is not documented during the control procurement process', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(795, 1, 3, 1, 'What is/are the main difference(s) between Performance Review and an Inspection?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Both options 1 & 2 outline the major differences between performance reviews & audits', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(796, 1, 3, 1, 'Petal has outsourced a work package of her project to an external vendor. What should be her next step?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Keyword is \"outsourced\". As the procure is in place, Petal has to control procurements next', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `category_id`, `sub_category_id`, `course_id`, `title`, `question_type`, `marks`, `dificulty_level`, `explanation`, `status`, `assessment_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `silver_set`, `gold_set`) VALUES
(797, 2, 6, 1, 'Petal has outsourced a work package of her project to an external vendor. What should be her next step?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Keyword is \"outsourced\". As the procure is in place, Petal has to control procurements next', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(798, 1, 3, 1, 'A claim can be resolved between both parties through a _________ before it is escalated to lawsuit.', 1, 1, NULL, 'Arbiration is the best option to resolve buy-seller disputes. This is done through alternate dispute resolution techniques. \n \n Sending legal notices or stopping delivery will only aggiviate the situation', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(799, 1, 3, 1, 'When should one use Inspection and Audit?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Procuement audits are conducted to ensure that the procured product/service meets the agreed standard', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(800, 1, 3, 1, 'When should one use Performance Review?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Performance reviews are done to ensure that the performance of the seller is as per the contract', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(801, 1, 3, 1, 'Why is Performance Reporting necessary at Control Procurement process?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Performance reviews are like appraisals for the sellers. It is to measure the level of contractual obligations of the seller', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(802, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following is TRUE?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Claims have to documented to ensure that all claims are reviewed & honoured. \n \n If they are documented, then there are chances that the claims may be misplaced or forgotten', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(803, 1, 3, 1, 'Payments to sellers should always be made according to the _______.', 1, 1, NULL, 'All payments are governed by the contract terms & conditions. It helps to main cordial buyer-seller relationship.\n \n Payments are not governed by conveniences of the involved parties', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(804, 1, 3, 1, 'Petal has replaced Jack as a project manager in an interior designing project. The painting work in the project is being done by ALF Interiors which has been a vendor of Petal\'s organization for last 3 years. However, Petal wants to make sure that whether she should outsource more work to ALF Interiors or not? Which should be of Petal\'s BEST help?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Performance review of the seller will provide more information for Petal to make an informed choice about seller\'s performance. This in turn will help her to decide the extent of outsourcing', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(805, 1, 3, 1, 'Which one of the following techniques explains the effects of risk interdependencies?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Decision tree analysis outlines the interdependecies among the risks. \n \n All other options are used to identify or analyse risks', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(806, 1, 3, 1, 'Jacob is a project manager to provide computerized system and internet connectivity in an old resort renovation project. Around 100 workstations will be installed, 200 network connections, 10 servers and 22 printers. They will be networked through LAN. All the risks have been identified and have gone through quantitative analysis. Also a contingency reserve has been created. One of the risks identified was \"Building owner must inspect the work which could cause additional delays or rework, the probability of it was 0.55 and impact USD -3,00.000.00. Jacob has identified that the building owner is taking more than the expected time and the risk is now affecting the project schedule and the probability of it is now 100%. What is the impact of the same on the project?', 1, 1, NULL, 'EMV = Probabiliy x impact amount = 1.00 x 3,00,000.00\n Also there will be more schedule delays if the inspection is not completed quickly.\n \n Both A & B are correct here', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(807, 1, 3, 1, 'Jacob is a project manager to provide entire computerized system and internet connectivity in an old resort renovation project. Around 100 workstations will be installed, 200 network connections, 10 servers and 22 printers. They will be networked through LAN. All the risks have been identified and have gone through quantitative analysis. Also a contingency reserve has been created. One of the risks identified was \"Building owner must inspect the work which could cause additional delays or rework, the probability of it was 0.55 and impact USD -3,00.000.00\". The other risk identified was \"The network printers need to be centrally located, but the cables should not be visible, with a probability of 50% and impact of USD -7,50,000.00\". Jacob has identified that the cabling risk will actually cost USD 9,00,000.00. What is the impact of the same in the project if both the risk happens?', 1, 1, NULL, 'When both the risks occur, then contigency reserve will be reduced by $3,00,000+$9,00,000=$12,00,000. There will also be schedule delays. \n \n Both A & B are correct here', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(808, 1, 3, 1, 'Perilya is a project manager in a software development project. After the completion of every milestone, she does identify new risks and also confirms that the risks are the risk register still apply to the project. Which tool is she using?', 1, 1, NULL, 'New risks are identified only during risk reassments. \n \n Secondary risks & Residual risks are also identified', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(809, 1, 3, 1, 'Perilya is a project manager in a software development project. She checks to confirm that the software has all the features built in that she wanted. However, she identifies that one of the features is missing and realized that a new risk has come up - missing feature which was to be developed as per functional specifications. Which tool is she using?', 1, 1, NULL, '\"Checks to confirm\" is the key here. Perilya is conducting Technical Performance Measurement.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(810, 1, 3, 1, 'Perilya is a project manager in a software development project. She asks her newly appointed risk expert Petal to relook at the risk response strategies. She identifies that few secondary risks that might be caused by the risk responses planned are missing. She updates the risk register accordingly. Which tool is she using?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Petal is reviewing the Risk Management process. She is auditing the process & unearthing secondary and/or residual risks', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(811, 1, 3, 1, 'Perilya is a project manager in a software development project. She is going through all the risk events in the project and plans to implement a risk response that would cost INR 1,50,000. She also cross checks to make sure that she has enough money left to cover the rest of the risks that might happen in future. Which tool is she using?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Perilya is reviewing the contingeny resrves burned on responding to known unknowns. \n \n She is conducting reserve analysis', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(812, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following is NOT done at Control Risks?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Risk responses are planned during Risk Response Planning & not durinf controlling risks. \n \n Residual risks, effectiveness of risk management plan are done during risk controlling', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(813, 1, 3, 1, 'The purpose of the review of deliverables and project performance at the conclusion of a project phase is to:', 1, 1, NULL, 'Phase End/Release End reviews would be done to analyze the feasibility and justification for project continuation. It will also be done during sprint retrospectives', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(814, 2, 6, 1, 'The purpose of the review of deliverables and project performance at the conclusion of a project phase is to:', 1, 1, NULL, 'Phase End/Release End reviews would be done to analyze the feasibility and justification for project continuation. It will also be done during sprint retrospectives', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(815, 1, 3, 1, 'A project is considered complete when the :', 1, 1, NULL, 'The Project is complete when BAC(Budget At Completion i.e. Estimated Project Cost+Contingency Reserve) is equal to the EV(Budget value of actual work done) which means the budgeted work is completed.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(816, 2, 6, 1, 'A project is considered complete when the :', 1, 1, NULL, 'The Project is complete when BAC(Budget At Completion i.e. Estimated Project Cost+Contingency Reserve) is equal to the EV(Budget value of actual work done) which means the budgeted work is completed.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(817, 1, 3, 1, 'Each project phase is marked by completion of one or more:', 1, 1, NULL, 'The Project is divided into phases based on key deliverable(s) that are to be delivered. The governance & tracking the progress of these key deliverables is the main purpose of having project phases.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(818, 2, 6, 1, 'Each project phase is marked by completion of one or more:', 1, 1, NULL, 'The Project is divided into phases based on key deliverable(s) that are to be delivered. The governance & tracking the progress of these key deliverables is the main purpose of having project phases.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(819, 1, 3, 1, 'The project closing process is essential to overall project planning. What is considered one of the most important steps in closing the project?', 1, 1, NULL, 'The Project can be closed only after all the contractual obligations are fulfilled. The project cannot be closed even if any one contractual obligation is not fulfilled.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(820, 2, 6, 1, 'The project closing process is essential to overall project planning. What is considered one of the most important steps in closing the project?', 1, 1, NULL, 'The Project can be closed only after all the contractual obligations are fulfilled. The project cannot be closed even if any one contractual obligation is not fulfilled.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(821, 1, 3, 1, 'Formal acceptance by the client or the sponsor of the project indicates that they have accepted the products of the project. This document should be signed off during which phase of the project?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Formal acceptance is done only during Administrative Closure (Formally closed). During Scope Validation or UAT deliverables are tested against the acceptance criteria outlined in the RTM', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(822, 2, 6, 1, 'Formal acceptance by the client or the sponsor of the project indicates that they have accepted the products of the project. This document should be signed off during which phase of the project?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Formal acceptance is done only during Administrative Closure (Formally closed). During Scope Validation or UAT deliverables are tested against the acceptance criteria outlined in the RTM', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(823, 1, 1, 1, 'Historical records during close-out are useful to __________ and ____________ for future projects:', 1, 1, NULL, 'Historical records including Lessons learned are use to highlight the issues and/or for trend predictions', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(824, 2, 6, 1, 'Historical records during close-out are useful to __________ and ____________ for future projects:', 1, 1, NULL, 'Historical records including Lessons learned are use to highlight the issues and/or for trend predictions', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(825, 1, 3, 1, 'Part of the project closure process is to gain formal acceptance. From whom do you need to gain this formal acceptance?', 1, 1, NULL, 'It is the customer (or the core stakeholder that provided the product/service requirements) should provide formal acceptance/sign-off', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(826, 2, 6, 1, 'Part of the project closure process is to gain formal acceptance. From whom do you need to gain this formal acceptance?', 1, 1, NULL, 'It is the customer (or the core stakeholder that provided the product/service requirements) should provide formal acceptance/sign-off', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(827, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following would be the most appropriate thing to do during the closing process group?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Project performance reviews are done during closure. All other options are done during monitor & control domain', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(828, 2, 6, 1, 'Which of the following would be the most appropriate thing to do during the closing process group?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Project performance reviews are done during closure. All other options are done during monitor & control domain', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(829, 1, 3, 1, 'The customer on a project tells the PM that he has run out of money to pay for the project. What should the PM do first?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Key words are \"which action is done first?\". Steer Comm is the most appropriate body empowered to decide the further course of action', 0, 16, '7778-07-02 09:09:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(830, 2, 6, 1, 'The customer on a project tells the PM that he has run out of money to pay for the project. What should the PM do first?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Key words are \"which action is done first?\". Steer Comm is the most appropriate body empowered to decide the further course of action', 0, 16, '7778-07-02 09:09:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(831, 3, 12, 1, 'The customer on a project tells the PM that he has run out of money to pay for the project. What should the PM do first?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Key words are \"which action is done first?\". Steer Comm is the most appropriate body empowered to decide the further course of action', 0, 16, '7778-07-02 09:09:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(832, 1, 3, 1, 'The customer has accepted the completed project scope. However, the lesson learned required by the project management office have not been completed. What is the status of the project?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Project status is incomplete till all the activities / processes are completed', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(833, 2, 6, 1, 'The customer has accepted the completed project scope. However, the lesson learned required by the project management office have not been completed. What is the status of the project?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Project status is incomplete till all the activities / processes are completed', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(834, 3, 12, 1, 'The customer has accepted the completed project scope. However, the lesson learned required by the project management office have not been completed. What is the status of the project?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Project status is incomplete till all the activities / processes are completed', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(835, 1, 3, 1, 'All the following are always part of the close project/phase process EXCEPT:', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Close Procurement is done in Control Procurement process that is in Monitor & Control domain. All other options are done during closure', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(836, 2, 6, 1, 'All the following are always part of the close project/phase process EXCEPT:', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Close Procurement is done in Control Procurement process that is in Monitor & Control domain. All other options are done during closure', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(837, 3, 12, 1, 'All the following are always part of the close project/phase process EXCEPT:', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Close Procurement is done in Control Procurement process that is in Monitor & Control domain. All other options are done during closure', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
