(1038, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following is the correct order of the Monitoring & Controlling processes for Scope Management?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Both the processes happen simultaneously as both include minimizing scope creep & gold plating', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1039, 1, 3, 1, 'Phyla has replaced Jack as the project manager of a telecom project. The project is going in a satisfactory manner in terms of time and budget. She is now using ETC and EAC calculations for future. ETC and EAC are used for?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Jack was using EVM to measure project performance. It can be assumed that time & budget are satisfactory as SPI & CPI are below 1. So the next step in EVM is to look at forecasts that include EAC (Estimate At Completion), ETC (Estimate to Complete) & TCPI (To Complete Performance Index)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1040, 1, 3, 1, 'Phyla is working as a Project Manager in an IT company. She is using historical data as the basis for estimating future outcomes of her project. Which forecasting methods is she using?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'By definition: Time series forecasting is the use of a model to predict future values based on previously observed values. i.e. Time Series method includes forecasting future outcomes based on historical data (previous project data)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1041, 1, 3, 1, 'Jasmine is working on a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of INR 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that INR 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. Her project sponsor has asked for the budgeted value for the project work actually completed by this point of time. Which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Key words here are \"work actually completed\" which means EV. Here is the math:\n EAC = INR 8,50,000\n PV=40% of 8,50,000 = INR 3,40,000\n EV=35% of 8,50,000 = INR 2,97,000\n AC=INR 4,25,000', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1042, 1, 2, 1, 'A project manager discovers a defect in a deliverable which is due to be submitted to the customer today. The project manager knows the customer does not have the technical understanding to notice the defect. The deliverable meets the contract requirements, but it does not meet the project manager\'s quality standard. What should the project manager do in this situation?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'This is more moral & ethical that does not meet or exceed PM\'s quality standard.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1043, 2, 9, 1, 'A project manager discovers a defect in a deliverable which is due to be submitted to the customer today. The project manager knows the customer does not have the technical understanding to notice the defect. The deliverable meets the contract requirements, but it does not meet the project manager\'s quality standard. What should the project manager do in this situation?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'This is more moral & ethical that does not meet or exceed PM\'s quality standard.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1044, 1, 3, 1, 'As a Project Manager for setting up a new manufacturing product line, part of your job is to determine if there are changes to the project scope, schedule, budget and technical requirements. These responsibilities are part of which process group:', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The question is updated (made the last word as \"process group\" instead of \"process\". \n \n Scope, budget, schedule, quality are all controlled in the M&C domain which includes measuring variance between baseline against actuals & trying to reduce it or keeping it under acceptable limits', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1045, 2, 6, 1, 'As a Project Manager for setting up a new manufacturing product line, part of your job is to determine if there are changes to the project scope, schedule, budget and technical requirements. These responsibilities are part of which process group:', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The question is updated (made the last word as \"process group\" instead of \"process\". \n \n Scope, budget, schedule, quality are all controlled in the M&C domain which includes measuring variance between baseline against actuals & trying to reduce it or keeping it under acceptable limits', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1046, 1, 3, 1, 'You are a project manager for developing a new desktop application software that will reduce time for document sharing. After you started working on the project, you thought of adding more reporting features, which the customer did not request. This is an example of:-', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'You are providing extra features or functionalities that the customer has not asked for nor it is part of Scope / WBS. You must be careful as gold plating often leads to other adverse impact on schedule, cost, quality, or scope', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1047, 2, 6, 1, 'You are a project manager for developing a new desktop application software that will reduce time for document sharing. After you started working on the project, you thought of adding more reporting features, which the customer did not request. This is an example of:-', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'You are providing extra features or functionalities that the customer has not asked for nor it is part of Scope / WBS. You must be careful as gold plating often leads to other adverse impact on schedule, cost, quality, or scope', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1048, 1, 3, 1, 'You have been appointed as a project manager of a project which is in trouble and to resolve it, you held a meeting with the key stakeholders in your company for demonstration of the new product prototype. They came well versed with the product requirements and upon inspection, inform you that this prototype is not what the customer has specified. Your boss instructs you to get the prototype corrected and match the requirements with customer specifications before holding a demo with the customer. She also wants you to take a look at the project work. She is concerned that things aren\'t happening as planned and that the last project manager was not paying close enough attention to the project plan. Corrections might be needed. What knowledge area does this describe?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Protype (or Proof of Concept) has to be built to demonstrate customer requirements being addressed/fulfilled. Requirements management, translating it to scope & controlling are processes of Scope Management KA', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1049, 1, 3, 1, 'A project manager\'s boss and the head of engineering department discuss change to a major task with the project manager. After the meeting, the boss contacts the project manager and tells him to make the change. This is an example of which of the following?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The question is not outlining CR or CCB, hence it is not change control. Management (Head of Engineering & PM\'s boss) are clearly paying attention to scope details', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1050, 2, 6, 1, 'A project manager\'s boss and the head of engineering department discuss change to a major task with the project manager. After the meeting, the boss contacts the project manager and tells him to make the change. This is an example of which of the following?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The question is not outlining CR or CCB, hence it is not change control. Management (Head of Engineering & PM\'s boss) are clearly paying attention to scope details', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1051, 1, 1, 1, 'You are in the middle of a new product development project for your publicly traded company. You have discovered that the previous project manager made a US $3,000,000 payment and it was not approved in accordance with your company policies. The project CPI is 1.2. What should you do?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Though project is under budget by 20% (CPI=1.2) at this point in time, You as PM are ethically & morally bound to report the breach of company policy', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1052, 2, 6, 1, 'You are in the middle of a new product development project for your publicly traded company. You have discovered that the previous project manager made a US $3,000,000 payment and it was not approved in accordance with your company policies. The project CPI is 1.2. What should you do?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Though project is under budget by 20% (CPI=1.2) at this point in time, You as PM are ethically & morally bound to report the breach of company policy', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1053, 1, 3, 1, 'You discovered that you have not planned for unknown risk events while preparing your risk responses. Now you are required to make adjustments to the project to compensate for known risk events. These adjustments are based on your past project experience when known risk events occurred and knocked the project off track. What should you do?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Changed \"Unknow\" to \"known\" risks in the question. Usually Contingent reserves are used to respond to known risks & management reserves are re used to respond to unknown risks.\n \n You cannot quantify the contingency reserve % as enough data is not provided. Hence is general contingency reserve is applied', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1054, 1, 3, 1, 'An organization is using non-linear probability impact scales for Risk assessment (ex: 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4, 0.8). What would this indicate?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The PI (or Severity) value is weighted by impact. The nonlinear Impact score means that High and Very High impact risks are always overweighed to give a higher PI, whereas Low and Very Low impact risks are underweighted to give a smaller product.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1055, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following is NOT true about configuration management ?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'This is a single negative question. NOT is the key word. CCB decisions do not come into play in configuration management', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1056, 2, 6, 1, 'Which of the following is NOT true about configuration management ?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'This is a single negative question. NOT is the key word. CCB decisions do not come into play in configuration management', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
