(1074, 1, 3, 1, 'You are in the middle of the project when you got to know that because of a new government regulation you will need to change your project\'s product specifications. What should you do next?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Government is the external stakeholder & the regulation (stakeholder requirement) is beyond your control. Raising CR is the first activity you perform.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1075, 2, 6, 1, 'You are in the middle of the project when you got to know that because of a new government regulation you will need to change your project\'s product specifications. What should you do next?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Government is the external stakeholder & the regulation (stakeholder requirement) is beyond your control. Raising CR is the first activity you perform.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1076, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following statements are FALSE regarding Monte Carlo analysis?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'Monte Carlo as the name suggests is a risk simulation technique used to identify high probability event occurrence (as in gambling). It does use not EMV where finite number of variables are used (only events most od the time). \n \n FALSE is the single negative that should not be missed.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1077, 1, 3, 1, 'Your customer has requested a change for which amendments in the contract are agreed upon and signed. For the requested changes, you have followed change control system and have modified the appropriate planning documents. As a result of the approved change, changes to the costs and schedule have also been made. Which of the following must occur next and why? Choose the BEST answer.', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'You do not make any changes to project docs unless the CR is approved by the CCB. The question outlines that the CR is approved and appropriate planning docs are updated. Next clear step is to update the baselines.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1078, 2, 6, 1, 'Your customer has requested a change for which amendments in the contract are agreed upon and signed. For the requested changes, you have followed change control system and have modified the appropriate planning documents. As a result of the approved change, changes to the costs and schedule have also been made. Which of the following must occur next and why? Choose the BEST answer.', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'You do not make any changes to project docs unless the CR is approved by the CCB. The question outlines that the CR is approved and appropriate planning docs are updated. Next clear step is to update the baselines.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1079, 1, 3, 1, 'Variance analysis , trend analysis and earned value management techniques are:-', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Variance, trend, or EV uses metrics that outline project performance. QC may use variance or trend, but not EVA. Cost Benefit is used mostly in cost management', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1080, 2, 8, 1, 'Variance analysis , trend analysis and earned value management techniques are:-', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Variance, trend, or EV uses metrics that outline project performance. QC may use variance or trend, but not EVA. Cost Benefit is used mostly in cost management', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1081, 1, 3, 1, 'What should the project manager be most concerned before moving to the final phase?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Project scope has to be validated (that reflects all applicable stakeholder requirements being fulfilled & accepted) before moving into the final phase.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1082, 1, 3, 1, 'A customer has provided you the scope of work for an eight-month project that has a few unknowns. The customer has asked you to just get it done and wants to see you only at the end of eight months i.e. when you deliver the finished project. Under these circumstances, which of the following is the best thing to do?', 1, 1, 'Complex', '\"Few unknowns\" is the key word here. So the PM would follow management by exception management style as customer has asked not to be contacted frequently. However it is a good practice to get the scope validated when a major deliverable has been produced & QC activities are completed. Customer can check the project viability at that points in time.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1083, 1, 3, 1, 'While executing a project, a deliverable has been submitted to the customer. The customer neither acknowledges the deliverable nor says if it is acceptable although an approval is required. What is the best thing to do in such a case?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Calling the team meeting or just documenting will not help in getting customer approval. Escalating the situation to the Management is the best action to take.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1084, 1, 3, 1, 'You are the project manager and your project has reached the end. Your project has been successful in terms of requirements, scope, schedule and cost. The functional manager under whom various team members used to work, is upset because many of his staff quit while working on the project. This is because of the long hours at the project and lack of management support. Which of the following is the MOST CORRECT statement about this project?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Many resources quit during the course of the project. This infers that the PM did not plan require requirement well & did not acquire (on board) enough resources & set their expectations/deadlines', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1085, 2, 6, 1, 'You are the project manager and your project has reached the end. Your project has been successful in terms of requirements, scope, schedule and cost. The functional manager under whom various team members used to work, is upset because many of his staff quit while working on the project. This is because of the long hours at the project and lack of management support. Which of the following is the MOST CORRECT statement about this project?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Many resources quit during the course of the project. This infers that the PM did not plan require requirement well & did not acquire (on board) enough resources & set their expectations/deadlines', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1086, 1, 3, 1, 'Management has assigned you a high priority project. You find it very difficult to finish the project with the available resources and scheduled time. Project manager talked to management to either assign more resource or change the end date. But management is not convinced. What should project manager do?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Always provide \"basis of estimates\" when any estimates are provide (time/budget/effort/resource estimates). For limited resource availability always provide the impact analysis that outline how muck work (%) can be completed by the available resources', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1087, 2, 6, 1, 'Management has assigned you a high priority project. You find it very difficult to finish the project with the available resources and scheduled time. Project manager talked to management to either assign more resource or change the end date. But management is not convinced. What should project manager do?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Always provide \"basis of estimates\" when any estimates are provide (time/budget/effort/resource estimates). For limited resource availability always provide the impact analysis that outline how muck work (%) can be completed by the available resources', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1088, 1, 3, 1, 'During project Executing you discover that you are working on a task requested by the customer but not included in the contract. The customer is already upset about the cost of several items she claims your company left out of the contract. No one in your company wants to discuss the change with the customer for fear of losing the contract. What is the best course of action in this case?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'Contract is driving the project & it\'s outcome. The contract has to be amended to cover all project deliverables (leading to tasks)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1089, 2, 6, 1, 'During project Executing you discover that you are working on a task requested by the customer but not included in the contract. The customer is already upset about the cost of several items she claims your company left out of the contract. No one in your company wants to discuss the change with the customer for fear of losing the contract. What is the best course of action in this case?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'Contract is driving the project & it\'s outcome. The contract has to be amended to cover all project deliverables (leading to tasks)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1090, 1, 2, 1, 'All the changes that needs to be done in scope must be written and approved. Which of the following conflict management strategy should you use if a team member tries to change the scope without approval?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'The team member is trying to change the scope unilaterally. We cannot punish, withdraw, or negotiate in such a situation. We have to enough research and try to resolve it by using problem solving technique', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1091, 2, 6, 1, 'All the changes that needs to be done in scope must be written and approved. Which of the following conflict management strategy should you use if a team member tries to change the scope without approval?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'The team member is trying to change the scope unilaterally. We cannot punish, withdraw, or negotiate in such a situation. We have to enough research and try to resolve it by using problem solving technique', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1092, 1, 3, 1, 'As you monitor your project progress, you discover that final deliverables cannot be completed as per the planned schedule. What should the project manager do?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'You are running the risk of schedule over run due to completion of final deliverables. You should look for options to reduce delays by schedule compression/utilizing unused floats/optimizing resources and/or dependencies', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1093, 2, 10, 1, 'As you monitor your project progress, you discover that final deliverables cannot be completed as per the planned schedule. What should the project manager do?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'You are running the risk of schedule over run due to completion of final deliverables. You should look for options to reduce delays by schedule compression/utilizing unused floats/optimizing resources and/or dependencies', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1094, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following is NOT needed to be done in case there is a major delay on a non-critical path activity?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'NOT is the keywork here. We do all other options except changing the project schedule', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1095, 2, 10, 1, 'Which of the following is NOT needed to be done in case there is a major delay on a non-critical path activity?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'NOT is the keywork here. We do all other options except changing the project schedule', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1096, 1, 3, 1, 'A big, multi-year construction project experienced weather related schedule delays which is supposed to be a typical for that area. Which of the following should project manager do to integrate this information into the project schedule?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'This is a typical delay & the weather related delay is bound to impact your project. Raising a CR will lead to impact analysis and once approved it can be integrated into the schedule', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1097, 1, 3, 1, 'You are the project manager of Friend Bees Pvt Ltd. The sponsor of your project has asked you to compress the schedule. Which of the following is CORRECT?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Correct is the keyword. In fast tracking the dependencies are to be re-evaluated to see if come activities can be completed in parallel rather than sequentially. And yes, crashing always leads to cost increase due to learning curve costs. (also law of diminishing returns)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1098, 2, 10, 1, 'You are the project manager of Friend Bees Pvt Ltd. The sponsor of your project has asked you to compress the schedule. Which of the following is CORRECT?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Correct is the keyword. In fast tracking the dependencies are to be re-evaluated to see if come activities can be completed in parallel rather than sequentially. And yes, crashing always leads to cost increase due to learning curve costs. (also law of diminishing returns)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1099, 1, 3, 1, 'Hazel is working on a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of USD 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that USD 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. Her project sponsor has asked for the difference between the budgeted value of the project work performed and where the project should have been at present. Please specify which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'BAC = $8,50,000\n EV = 35% of 8,50,000 = $2,97,500\n PV = 40% of 8,50,000 = $3,40,000\n SV = EV-PV = -42,500', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1100, 1, 3, 1, 'Phyla is working on a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of INR 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that INR 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. Her project sponsor has asked whether the project is on budget or not. Please specify which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'BAC = $8,50,000\n EV = 35% of 8,50,000 = $2,97,500\n PV = 40% of 8,50,000 = $3,40,000\n AC = $4,25,000\n CPI = EV/AC = 0.7', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1101, 1, 3, 1, 'Phyla is working on a project which has a Budget at Completion (BAC) of INR 8,50,000.00 and is 24 months long. As on date her project is 35% complete, while it was supposed to be 40% complete at present. She has also reported that INR 4,25,000.00 has already been spent on the project. Her project sponsor has asked whether the project is on schedule or not and if he is getting any value from the project. Please specify which statement is TRUE?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'BAC = $8,50,000\n EV = 35% of 8,50,000 = $2,97,500\n PV = 40% of 8,50,000 = $3,40,000\n AC = $4,25,000\n SPI = EV/PV = 0.875', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1102, 1, 3, 1, 'Phyla is working on a Project as a Project Manager. Her Earned Value is more than Actual Cost. Which statement holds TRUE?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'PV is not given, hence schedule metrics cannot be determined. The project has earned more than what is actually spent, hence is under budget', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1103, 1, 3, 1, 'Phyla is working on a Project as a Project Manager. Her Earned Value is less than Actual Cost. Which statement holds TRUE?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'PV is not given, hence schedule metrics cannot be determined. The project has earned less than what is actually spent, hence is over budget', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL);
