(1126, 1, 3, 1, 'Which of the following phase has maximum impact on product reliability and maintenance characteristics?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Product reliability & its sustenance (maintenance) attributes are considered whilst designing, hence it has maximum impact during design phase', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1127, 2, 6, 1, 'Which of the following phase has maximum impact on product reliability and maintenance characteristics?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Product reliability & its sustenance (maintenance) attributes are considered whilst designing, hence it has maximum impact during design phase', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1128, 1, 2, 1, 'Muddy is working as a manager in an Export House who want to develop an in-house, Customer Relationship Management Software. He finds that he needs to take approval from department head for each of project decisions. Which of the following is true about such functional organizations?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'All the three options outline the characteristics of functional organization', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1129, 2, 6, 1, 'Muddy is working as a manager in an Export House who want to develop an in-house, Customer Relationship Management Software. He finds that he needs to take approval from department head for each of project decisions. Which of the following is true about such functional organizations?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'All the three options outline the characteristics of functional organization', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1130, 1, 2, 1, 'Ramie is working as a project manager in Four-Wheeler CORP LTD located in Japan. For a new project, he has been assigned 10 resources and is required to release them after the project has been completed. He finds that he is working in a projectised organization. Who has the decision making power in such organizations?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'In projectized organization, all decisions are taken by the PM and PM has maximum authority', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1131, 2, 6, 1, 'Ramie is working as a project manager in Four-Wheeler CORP LTD located in Japan. For a new project, he has been assigned 10 resources and is required to release them after the project has been completed. He finds that he is working in a projectised organization. Who has the decision making power in such organizations?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'In projectized organization, all decisions are taken by the PM and PM has maximum authority', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1132, 1, 2, 1, 'Ramie is a working as a project manager in Four-Wheeler CORP LTD located in Japan. For a new project he has been assigned 10 resources and have to release them after the project is completed. All project management decision lies with him. Which of the following is true about such organizations?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'The project org team (OBS) structure is built around the project. Other Functional departments or its Managers have no or limited authority', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1133, 2, 6, 1, 'Ramie is a working as a project manager in Four-Wheeler CORP LTD located in Japan. For a new project he has been assigned 10 resources and have to release them after the project is completed. All project management decision lies with him. Which of the following is true about such organizations?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'The project org team (OBS) structure is built around the project. Other Functional departments or its Managers have no or limited authority', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1134, 1, 2, 1, 'Ramie is working as a project manager in Four-Wheeler CORP LTD located in Japan. For a new project, he has been assigned 10 resources and have to release them after the project is completed. All project management decisions lies with him. Which of the following is NOT true about such organizations?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Ramie has complete authority & control over the project. He is not working as the assistant to the Functional Managers.\n (Do not miss the key word \"NOT TRUE\")', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1135, 2, 6, 1, 'Ramie is working as a project manager in Four-Wheeler CORP LTD located in Japan. For a new project, he has been assigned 10 resources and have to release them after the project is completed. All project management decisions lies with him. Which of the following is NOT true about such organizations?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Ramie has complete authority & control over the project. He is not working as the assistant to the Functional Managers.\n (Do not miss the key word \"NOT TRUE\")', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1136, 1, 2, 1, 'Two project managers are working in different organizations. They were having dinner together and found that they are working in weak matrix organization. One finds that he is a project coordinator and other finds that he is a project expeditor. How does a project expeditor differ from project coordinator?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'PE\'s main role is the expedite the assigned work & they will not have any authority. PC\'s role is to co-ordinate all activities cutting across all Knowledge Areas. They will have limited authority that is required to co-ordinate project activities', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1137, 2, 6, 1, 'Two project managers are working in different organizations. They were having dinner together and found that they are working in weak matrix organization. One finds that he is a project coordinator and other finds that he is a project expeditor. How does a project expeditor differ from project coordinator?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'PE\'s main role is the expedite the assigned work & they will not have any authority. PC\'s role is to co-ordinate all activities cutting across all Knowledge Areas. They will have limited authority that is required to co-ordinate project activities', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1138, 1, 3, 1, 'You have been given responsibility of upgrading old server farm to the latest Quad Core Xeon Intel processors. The Up-gradation includes changing complete server hardware and may require restoring of data on these new servers. You ask PMO for historical records for similar projects that company has earlier worked upon. What are you making use of?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'You are referring to historical information from the process assets that were created in earlier projects. These are the OPAs you are referring to.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1139, 2, 6, 1, 'You have been given responsibility of upgrading old server farm to the latest Quad Core Xeon Intel processors. The Up-gradation includes changing complete server hardware and may require restoring of data on these new servers. You ask PMO for historical records for similar projects that company has earlier worked upon. What are you making use of?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'You are referring to historical information from the process assets that were created in earlier projects. These are the OPAs you are referring to.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1140, 1, 3, 1, 'You are currently working as manager in BCL Logistics. You have been given responsibility for moving Infrastructure of ABC Software IT CORP LTD to the newly procured office in Los Angeles. You have determined the overall cost for your project. What should be your next step?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'You have already computed the project cost (fixed costs, variable costs, resource costs, etc.). Next step is to compute the project budget by adding \"Management Reserve\" that can be used when unknown unknown events occur', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1141, 1, 3, 1, 'Jessie has just started working on a new IT project that has zero float. He is currently identifying risk for the project. Which of the following process deals with prioritizing risk for further analysis or action by assessing and combining their probability of occurrence and impact?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Jessie is not quantifying the risks as he is not using definitive numbers (Expected Monetary Value or sensitivity analysis) for analysis. He is computing Risk Severity (=P*I) which is qualifying the risk', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1142, 1, 3, 1, 'Jessie has just started working on a new IT project that has zero float. He is currently identifying risk for the project. Which of the following process deals numerically analyzing the effect of risk on overall project objective?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Jessie is quantifying the risks as he is using definitive numbers (Expected Monetary Value or sensitivity analysis) for analysis.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1143, 1, 3, 1, 'Jack has just taken over a project. He is currently identifying risk for the project. Which of the following process deals with developing option and actions to enhance opportunities and to reduce threats to the project objectives?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Jack is planning response options when the risk occurs. (Enhance, mitigate, escalate, accept, avoid, transfer, exploit, etc. are some risk response strategies)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1144, 1, 3, 1, 'Franklyn is working as a project manager in a Real Estate Company who are developing a state of the art commercial complex. He is currently working on Risk analysis. The kind of risks that the organization or stakeholders are willing to accept to an certain extent is known as:', 1, 1, NULL, 'Risks are accepted if the impact is within the threshold that is also known as risk tolerance', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1145, 1, 3, 1, 'You are just assigned a project. Though you are working in the organization for many years, still the project is new for you. The project performance till date is with in baseline thresholds, still customer is not happy. What would be the best action to be considered at the very outset:-', 1, 1, NULL, 'You have to reassess if the customer expectations are documented & are being fulfilled. Customer is not happy though the overall project performance metrics are within the baseline is because their needs and/or expectations are not being addressed', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1146, 1, 3, 1, 'Philip is working as a project manager for AUTOCARS PVT LTD. He is currently conducting meetings for creating the high level plan for creating the risk management activities. Which process is he currently working in?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Phillip is creating plan for risk management activities. This is done during \"Plan Risk Management\" PM process', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1147, 1, 3, 1, 'Phil has been assigned a new marketing project in BCL Marketing Pvt. Ltd. You are currently identifying risks. Which of the following people should be part of identifying risk process?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Entire project team is involved in identifying risks.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1148, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working as project manager in an Aerospace Firm and you are currently given in charge of manufacturing a new technology airplane which can cover 1500KM per hour. You are currently identifying risks. While checking Activity Cost Estimates , which of the following types of risks can be identified?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Known unknowns & unknown unknowns have to be considered during activity cost estimation process. This will help you to determine if the allocated funds are enough to complete the project', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1149, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working as project manager in an Aerospace Firm and you are currently given in charge of manufacturing a new technology airplane, which can cover 1500KM per hour. You are currently identifying risks, while checking Scope Baseline, which of the following types of risks can be identified?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Scope baseline consists of scope statement that outlines, in scope, out of scope, assumptions, and constraints. Option 1 is the right answer as cost or schedule risks cannot be identified whilst checking scope baseline', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1150, 1, 3, 1, 'Contingency allowance is fixed at 9% of total project cost to cover risks. When the project is near completion, total dollars in contingency reserve are:-', 1, 1, NULL, 'When the project is near completion (as outlined in the question), the contingency reserve that is quite significant (9%) will be removed / reduced to measure real percentage of work performed.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1151, 1, 3, 1, 'Suppose, the project manager is appointed to manage a new project that has just been given approval to start the planning requirements. The project manager is new to the organization and has inherited a project team previously selected by the top management. The best method of initiating the communication process with the team and to establish the expectations of the project team is to __________________', 1, 1, NULL, 'Project kick-off is the ideal forum for breaking ice & get to know each other. After initial introductions and determining strengths & weaknesses, work can be assigned based on resource availability and capability', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1152, 1, 3, 1, 'To come out with staffing requirement , Project Manager first needs:-', 1, 1, NULL, 'WBS is the main artefact that outlines the work required for every project deliverable. Staffing levels cannot be determined if the exact required project work is not available & WBS provides it', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1153, 1, 3, 1, 'Russell is working as a project manager in KWSoft.com. You are currently identifying risks by using information gathering techniques. Which of the following is NOT an information gathering diagramming technique that can be used to identify risks?', 1, 1, NULL, 'NOT is the keywork here. SWOT (Strengths, Weaknesses, Opportunities, & Threats) is not an information gathering technique but is a data analysis technique', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1154, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working as a manager in a chemical firm. Your company has received an order of delivering a chemical that is highly sensitive at room temperature and requires (-)10 degree centigrade temperature for storage. You have been given responsibility of making this chemical from the compound manufacture and delivered to you by a firm that is 500KM away from your location. You are currently identifying risks for your project. Which of the following technique is used to identify any opportunities arising from organizational strengths and any threats arising from organizational weakness?', 1, 1, NULL, 'You are analyzing opportunities arising from organizational strengths and any threats arising from organizational weakness. This is SWOT analysis', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1155, 1, 3, 1, 'Natasha has been assigned a new telecom project as a project manager. Her project team and stakeholders are based out of different locations. She has 6 team members, 2 sponsors, and 1 client. She wants to inform all of them about the progress of her project. How many communication channels will she have?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Natasha+6 team members+2 sponsors+1 client = 10 stakeholders\n \n # Comm channels = [10*(10-1)]/2 = 45', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1156, 2, 8, 1, 'Natasha has been assigned a new telecom project as a project manager. Her project team and stakeholders are based out of different locations. She has 6 team members, 2 sponsors, and 1 client. She wants to inform all of them about the progress of her project. How many communication channels will she have?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Natasha+6 team members+2 sponsors+1 client = 10 stakeholders\n \n # Comm channels = [10*(10-1)]/2 = 45', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1157, 1, 3, 1, 'Due to recent recession, 5 out of 8 of Jack\'s project team members have been laid off. There are 3 sponsors in his project. How many communication channels does Jack have in his new team?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Jack\'s team is left with 3 members + 3 sponsors + Jack = 7\n \n # Comm channels = (7*6)/2 = 21', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1158, 2, 8, 1, 'Due to recent recession, 5 out of 8 of Jack\'s project team members have been laid off. There are 3 sponsors in his project. How many communication channels does Jack have in his new team?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Jack\'s team is left with 3 members + 3 sponsors + Jack = 7\n \n # Comm channels = (7*6)/2 = 21', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1159, 1, 3, 1, '3 members have been added in Natasha\'s team. Now she has 7 team members, 1 sponsor and 1 client. How many communication lines have been added?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Before, 4 team members+1 sponsor+ 1 client + Natasha=7 stakeholders & 21 comm channels\n \n After, 7 team members+1 sponsor+ 1 client + Natasha=10 stakeholders & 45 comm channels\n \n 45-21 = 24 comm channels have been added', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1160, 2, 8, 1, '3 members have been added in Natasha\'s team. Now she has 7 team members, 1 sponsor and 1 client. How many communication lines have been added?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Before, 4 team members+1 sponsor+ 1 client + Natasha=7 stakeholders & 21 comm channels\n \n After, 7 team members+1 sponsor+ 1 client + Natasha=10 stakeholders & 45 comm channels\n \n 45-21 = 24 comm channels have been added', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1161, 1, 3, 1, 'Natasha is working in a project where the next phase can start only when the previous phase is 100% complete. What does this mean?', 1, 1, NULL, 'the project life cycle has sequential phases & earlier phase has to be completed, pass through a phase gate before next phase is initiated (phase gate is applicable in most of the cases though not explicitly mentioned in the question)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1162, 2, 10, 1, 'Natasha is working in a project where the next phase can start only when the previous phase is 100% complete. What does this mean?', 1, 1, NULL, 'the project life cycle has sequential phases & earlier phase has to be completed, pass through a phase gate before next phase is initiated (phase gate is applicable in most of the cases though not explicitly mentioned in the question)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1163, 1, 3, 1, 'Shirley has been assigned a project where she is required to install new computers in the office and have Windows 7 as the Operating System in all of them. She is required to install 100 computers and similar number of operating systems. She has two teams working on it. One, which will install the computers and the other will install the operating system in the computer. When the first team has installed 10 computers, the other team has started to install the Operating Systems in the new installed computer. What does this mean?', 1, 1, NULL, 'OS upgrades are not waiting for all 100 computer hardware to be upgraded. Both the phases are overlapping', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1164, 2, 10, 1, 'Shirley has been assigned a project where she is required to install new computers in the office and have Windows 7 as the Operating System in all of them. She is required to install 100 computers and similar number of operating systems. She has two teams working on it. One, which will install the computers and the other will install the operating system in the computer. When the first team has installed 10 computers, the other team has started to install the Operating Systems in the new installed computer. What does this mean?', 1, 1, NULL, 'OS upgrades are not waiting for all 100 computer hardware to be upgraded. Both the phases are overlapping', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1165, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working in ABC Enterprises and just been promoted to Project manager. You have been assigned a new project. Which of the following is NOT a characteristic of a Project?', 1, 1, NULL, 'NOT is the key. Project is not ongoing as operations', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
