(1167, 1, 2, 1, 'Barriers to communication can be invisible to a casual observer but can often be greater obstacles than physical barriers. However, barriers do not include-', 1, 1, NULL, 'Technical approach is not considered a communication barrier. Do not miss \"NOT Include\" in the question', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1168, 2, 6, 1, 'Barriers to communication can be invisible to a casual observer but can often be greater obstacles than physical barriers. However, barriers do not include-', 1, 1, NULL, 'Technical approach is not considered a communication barrier. Do not miss \"NOT Include\" in the question', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1169, 1, 3, 1, 'Project is in execution phase. It has however run into various unexpected problems. Many of the risks have surfaced which you did not think earlier. The project is already behind schedule and has gone over-budget. What should be done?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Many new risks that were not identified have surfaced. Additional risks have to identified immediately. Risk analysis will follow', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1170, 1, 3, 1, 'Renee is working as project manager in a Pharmaceutical Company. While executing the project, he finds certain events that can change the outcome of certain activities. Which of the following is a way to handle RISK? Choose the best answer.', 1, 1, NULL, 'All risk responses have to be considered in this case', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1171, 1, 3, 1, 'Thomas is a project manager working on a construction project near New York City. While project executing, Thomas find certain events that can change the outcome of certain activities. He decided to reduce the impact of the event. Which of the following way he has chosen to handle RISK?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Reducing the magnitude of impact due to occurrence of an uncertain event is the mitigation. It is acceptance as some minimum impact will remain after risk mitigation', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1172, 1, 3, 1, 'Rick has been promoted to Project Manager. He is currently working on a Project involving new technologies. While project executing, you find certain events that can change the outcome of certain activities. You decided to reduce the impact of the event and bought an insurance policy to cover the risk. Which of the following way he has chosen to handle RISK?', 1, 1, NULL, 'Rick is transferring the risk impact to a third party by insuring the activity (purchasing the insurance policy to cover for the loss due to high impact)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1173, 1, 3, 1, 'A diagram that explains the decision taken and implications of choosing it over other available alternatives, helps in:-', 1, 1, NULL, 'EMV is a decision tree analysis tool that numerically analyzes that out come of every decision and helps determine the greatest expected value (highest EMV)', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1174, 1, 3, 1, 'Michael is working as a Manager in Printing Press of large Printing House. He decided to put a surge protector to make sure lightning wont blow out the electrical instruments. Which of the following way he has chosen to handle RISK?', 1, 1, NULL, 'The surge protector will reduce the impact & power overloading on the electrical instruments.\n \n Electrical instruments will not be used if \"Avoid\" option is considered', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1175, 1, 3, 1, 'Jack has just taken over a project. He is now currently identifying risks in the project. He gets all Team member in a room and started to pump out ideas. Which among the following information gathering techniques is he using?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Jack is encouraging all teams members to provide their inputs in identifying risks. He is not masking the identity of the team members as in Delphi technique. He is not conducting 1 on 1s as in interviews.', 0, 16, '7778-07-02 09:09:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1176, 3, 12, 1, 'Jack has just taken over a project. He is now currently identifying risks in the project. He gets all Team member in a room and started to pump out ideas. Which among the following information gathering techniques is he using?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Jack is encouraging all teams members to provide their inputs in identifying risks. He is not masking the identity of the team members as in Delphi technique. He is not conducting 1 on 1s as in interviews.', 0, 16, '7778-07-02 09:09:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1177, 1, 3, 1, 'You are Project Manager working in IT CORP LTD. You have been assigned a new project of Inventory management System. You are currently identifying risks in your project. You decided to send questionnaires to experts asking about important project risks. Which type of the following information gathering technique is he using?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'You are gathering inputs without other team members knowing the identity of the team member providing inputs which is Delphi technique.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1178, 3, 12, 1, 'You are Project Manager working in IT CORP LTD. You have been assigned a new project of Inventory management System. You are currently identifying risks in your project. You decided to send questionnaires to experts asking about important project risks. Which type of the following information gathering technique is he using?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'You are gathering inputs without other team members knowing the identity of the team member providing inputs which is Delphi technique.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1179, 1, 3, 1, 'You are Project Manager working in IT CORP LTD. You have been assigned a new project on Inventory management System. You are currently identifying risks in your project by looking at plans, requirements and documents from your organization process assets. Which type of the identify risk technique you are using?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'You are reviewing historical information of similar past projects to identify potential risks that may be applicable for the current project. You are using \"Document Review\" technique.\n \n You are neither analyzing assumptions/constraints nor doing SWOT analysis not analyzing checklists', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
