(1190, 1, 3, 1, 'You work as project manager for a construction company and you are at a stage in the project where you have to decide whether to lease or rent the construction equipment. Leasing requires an base investment of $40,000 followed by a charge of $120/day. However renting costs $200/day. How many days will it be until leasing becomes more economical than renting?', 1, 1, 'Complex', '40,000 + 120x = 200x\n X= 500 days\n \n Intial Investment + Cost per day for lease needs to be equal to cost per day of the rent.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1191, 3, 12, 1, 'You work as project manager for a construction company and you are at a stage in the project where you have to decide whether to lease or rent the construction equipment. Leasing requires an base investment of $40,000 followed by a charge of $120/day. However renting costs $200/day. How many days will it be until leasing becomes more economical than renting?', 1, 1, 'Complex', '40,000 + 120x = 200x\n X= 500 days\n \n Intial Investment + Cost per day for lease needs to be equal to cost per day of the rent.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1192, 1, 3, 1, 'Jerry is managing a project which is running little behind schedule because a key resource took an unexpected leave of absence. The resource will be resuming next week and will make up for the lost time. Meanwhile, Jerry has not been able to complete his assessment of the project delay. However, as the delay is only minor and is expected to be covered next week. Jerry does not want to unnecessarily worry the project stakeholders. What will be his project status report for the meeting?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Project manager needs to report and be 100 % transparent and truthful in the reports. If the reports are true, some stakeholders may not like the same but Project Manger will get needed support in the interest of the project. In the current scenario, option B is the best choice with the PM.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 10. Project Communication Management / Project Communications Plan, pp359-362', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
