(1198, 1, 2, 1, 'PM complained to project sponsor that he did not get the correct number of resources as planned. Sponsor agreed the PMs complaint is genuine and decided to cancel the project. Which process would have prevented this extreme step from Project Sponsor?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'The resource management plan is used to help determine how resources allocated to agreed-upon risk responses will be coordinated with other project resources. This will provide guidance as to how the project manager can negotiate with the resource\'s manager. PM needs to acquire right resources for him to manage the project well failing which all the estimates will go wrong leading to failure of the project.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), Project Resource Management / 9.3.1 Acquire Resources: Inputs, p330', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
