(1213, 1, 3, 1, 'One of the modules of Kaya\'s project is to create a social networking platform, where the users are posting questions, writing blogs, and reviewing the comments of users. Which technique defines this type of scenario?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'From an organizational perspective, knowledge management is about making sure the skills, experience, and expertise of the project team and other stakeholders are used before, during, and after the project. Because knowledge resides in the minds of people and people cannot be forced to share what they know (or to pay attention to others knowledge), the most important part of knowledge management is creating an atmosphere of trust so that people are motivated to share\n their knowledge.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 9. Project Integration Management / 4.4 MANAGE PROJECT KNOWLEDGE, pp 133\n  | Knowledge management, 133, 365', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
