(1236, 1, 3, 1, 'Sam is building a multi-story government apartment with his construction company. He is in the process of ensuring that the team follows the risk management policies. Which process is he currently in?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The key words here are process of ensuring. This is a monitoring and control. Hence the best choice is D.\n Monitor Risks is the process of monitoring the implementation of agreed-upon risk response plans, tracking identified risks, identifying and analyzing new risks, and evaluating risk process effectiveness throughout the project.\n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), Part 2 The Standard for Project Management / 11.7 Monitor Risk, Page 490', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1237, 3, 12, 1, 'Sam is building a multi-story government apartment with his construction company. He is in the process of ensuring that the team follows the risk management policies. Which process is he currently in?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The key words here are process of ensuring. This is a monitoring and control. Hence the best choice is D.\n Monitor Risks is the process of monitoring the implementation of agreed-upon risk response plans, tracking identified risks, identifying and analyzing new risks, and evaluating risk process effectiveness throughout the project.\n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), Part 2 The Standard for Project Management / 11.7 Monitor Risk, Page 490', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1238, 1, 3, 1, 'Michael is a project manager working on a project. He finds out that several regulatory requirements have not captured in the requirements document. If those requirements are met, his project will exceed its budget, scope, duration, and possibly get cancelled. What should Michael do in this scenario?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Any changes to baseline needs to be handled via change request. Regulatory requirments are mandatory requirements and needs to be handled immediately. Best choice is option A\n \n Perform Integrated Change Control is the process of reviewing all change requests; approving changes and managing changes to deliverables, project documents, and the project management plan; and communicating the decisions. This process reviews all requests for changes to project documents, deliverables, or the project management plan and determines the resolution of the change requests. The key benefit of this process is that it allows for documented changes within the project to be considered in an integrated manner while addressing overall project risk, which often arises from changes made without consideration of the overall project objectives or plans. This process is performed throughout the project.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), Part 2 The Standard for Project Management / 4.6 Perform Integrated change control , Page 150', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
