(1241, 1, 3, 1, 'Sal is a project manager in biochemical organization. In his industry, identification of risk is the highest priority. To achieve this, he wants to make sure he gets unbiased response from all the critical and non-critical stakeholders on his project. What is the most appropriate technique Sal can use to identify project risks?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Interviews. An interview is a formal or informal approach to elicit information from stakeholders by talking to them directly. It is typically performed by asking prepared and spontaneous questions and recording the responses. \n Assumption and constraint analysis explores the validity of assumptions and constraints to determine which pose a risk to the project.\n Brainstorming. This technique is used to identify a list of ideas in a short period of time. It is conducted in a group environment and is led by a facilitator.\n Delphi method is a forecasting process framework based on the results of multiple rounds of questionnaires sent to a panel of experts. Several rounds of questionnaires are sent out to the group of experts, and the anonymous responses are aggregated and shared with the group after each round.\n \n Given the current scenario SAL should use interviews to identify the risks. Best choice by defination is option A.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
