(1246, 1, 3, 1, 'You are bidding for a contract, however, you are not clear on one of the critical components of the Request for Proposal (RFP). One of your professional references with whom you have worked in the past offers to provide his professional expertise. What will be the advantage of using his service?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Independent cost estimates help understand and offer best solution.The procuring organization may elect to either prepare its own independent estimate or have a cost estimate prepared by an outside professional estimator to serve as a benchmark on proposed responses. Significant differences in cost estimates can be an indication that the procurement SOW was deficient or ambiguous, or that the prospective sellers either misunderstood or failed to respond fully to the procurement SOW.\n Best choice is option D.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 13. Project Stakeholder Management / 12.1.3.7 Independent cost estimates, p503', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
