(1248, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working on a project where you have outsourced the work to a seller\'s company. Based on your discussion with the seller, you are revisiting your project assumptions defined in the scope statement to check whether they are still valid or not. Which process are you currently performing?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Since you are revisiting your project assumptions defined in the scope statement, means PM is monitoring Risk and will take actions as needed. Hence the best choice is D.\n Monitor Risks is the process of monitoring the implementation of agreed-upon risk response plans, tracking identified risks, identifying and analyzing new risks, and evaluating risk process effectiveness throughout the project.\n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), Part 2 The Standard for Project Management / 11.7 Monitor Risk, Page 490', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
