(1250, 1, 2, 1, 'A successful project manager should be both proficient at work and at managing relationships. To maintain good relationships, nterpersonal skills are important. Which of the following is not an interpersonal skill?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Project managers accomplish work through the project team and other stakeholders. Project managers rely on important interpersonal skills, including, but not limited to: Leadership, Team building, Motivating, Communicating, Influencing, Decision making, Political and cultural awareness, Negotiating, Facilitating, Managing conflict, and Coaching.\n Resisting change cannot be an interpersonal skill. Best choice is D.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
