(1270, 1, 3, 1, 'Mahesh works as project manager for a construction company. His company has secured a new contract to remodel a kitchen in two months. The budget of the project is $10,000. Before awarding the contract to Mahesh\'s company, the client informs him that the scope is well-defined lord the project. For this scenario, which contract type in recommended?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'Fixed price contractss are the most favored for buying organizations because the price for goods is set at the outset and not subject to change unless the scope\n of work changes.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 12. Project Risk Management /12.1.1.6 Contract Types, p508', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
