(1287, 1, 3, 1, 'Buns is a senior software engineer. His company plans to launch the Google Pay feature on their app so that the end user can pay for orders in a more convenient fashion. The team is working on the scope baseline and it is almost complete. All of the following are parts of the scope baseline except', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'The scope management plan is a component of the project or program management plan that describes how the scope will be defined, developed, monitored, controlled, and validated. The development of the scope management plan and the detailing of the project scope begin with the analysis of information contained in the project charter the latest approved subsidiary plans of the project management plan, historical information contained in the organizational process assets, and any other relevant enterprise environmental factors.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 5. Project Scope Management / 5.1 Plan scope management , pp 171', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
