(1297, 1, 3, 1, 'You are in the process of creating an activity list. One of your colleagues recommends that you subdivide the project into smaller components, called activities. Which tool are they talking about?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Decomposition is a technique used for dividing and subdividing the project scope and project deliverables into smaller, more manageable parts. The work package is the work defined at the lowest level of the WBS for which cost and duration can be estimated and managed. The level of decomposition is often guided by the degree of control needed to effectively manage the project. The level of detail for work packages will vary with the size and complexity of the project. \n \n  PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) 5. Project Scope Management / 5.4.2.2 DECOMPOSITION, p195', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
