(1307, 1, 3, 1, 'Mary is at a senior position in the procurement team. She only gets Involved if there is major escalation. It so happens that the team is not happy with the way a vendor is currently working on the project. Stacy, another project manager reaches out to Mary to discuss the performance of the vendor. Which process is Stacy performing?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Control Procurements is the process of managing procurement relationships; monitoring contract performance, and making changes and corrections as appropriate; and closing out contracts. The key benefit of this process is that it ensures that both the sellers and buyers performance meet the projects requirements according to the terms of the legal agreement. This process is performed throughout the project as needed. Best choice as PM is trying to manage issues in the project. Best choice is B.\n \n  PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) 12. Project Procurement Management / 12.3 CONTROL PROCUREMENTS, p529', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1308, 3, 12, 1, 'Mary is at a senior position in the procurement team. She only gets Involved if there is major escalation. It so happens that the team is not happy with the way a vendor is currently working on the project. Stacy, another project manager reaches out to Mary to discuss the performance of the vendor. Which process is Stacy performing?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Control Procurements is the process of managing procurement relationships; monitoring contract performance, and making changes and corrections as appropriate; and closing out contracts. The key benefit of this process is that it ensures that both the sellers and buyers performance meet the projects requirements according to the terms of the legal agreement. This process is performed throughout the project as needed. Best choice as PM is trying to manage issues in the project. Best choice is B.\n \n  PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) 12. Project Procurement Management / 12.3 CONTROL PROCUREMENTS, p529', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1309, 1, 3, 1, 'Your organization has quality standards that need to be implemented for each project. In which process can you achieve this?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Manage Quality is the process of translating the quality management plan into executable quality activities that incorporate the organizations quality policies into the project. The key benefits of this process are that it increases the probability of meeting the quality objectives as well as identifying ineffective processes and causes of poor quality. Manage Quality uses the data and results from the control quality process to reflect the overall quality status of the project to the stakeholders. This process is performed throughout the project and all the projects need to do the same. Best choice is C.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 8. Project Quality Management / 8.2 MANAGE QUALITY pp325', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
