(1315, 1, 3, 1, 'The total budget for your project is $200,000 and there is a total of 1000 hours of work scheduled to be completed during the project. At this point, you have spent $30,000 and you should have completed 300 hours worth of work. However one of your critical resources is not allocated 100% on this project which has resulted in completion of only 200 hours, worth of work. What is projects status?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Cost per day = 200000/1000= 200\n EV = 200 *200= 40000\n PV= 300*200= 60000\n AC= 30000\n CPI = EV/AC = 1.3\n SPI= EV/PV=0.6\n \n Best choice is A.\n  \n A CPI over 1 means the project is under budget and SPI under 1 means Behind schedule.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2017), 7. Project Cost Management / 7.4.2 Control Costs: Tools and Techniques, pp260-263', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1316, 3, 12, 1, 'The total budget for your project is $200,000 and there is a total of 1000 hours of work scheduled to be completed during the project. At this point, you have spent $30,000 and you should have completed 300 hours worth of work. However one of your critical resources is not allocated 100% on this project which has resulted in completion of only 200 hours, worth of work. What is projects status?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Cost per day = 200000/1000= 200\n EV = 200 *200= 40000\n PV= 300*200= 60000\n AC= 30000\n CPI = EV/AC = 1.3\n SPI= EV/PV=0.6\n \n Best choice is A.\n  \n A CPI over 1 means the project is under budget and SPI under 1 means Behind schedule.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2017), 7. Project Cost Management / 7.4.2 Control Costs: Tools and Techniques, pp260-263', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1317, 1, 2, 1, 'You are a project manager of a transformation project. Initially, the team was not collaborative and open to different ideas and perspectives which created a counterproductive environment. However, you work with your team lead and the situation improves. The environment improving and team is wanting to collaborate. Which stage is your project in?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Forming. This phase is where the team members meet and learn about the project and their formal roles and responsibilities. Team members tend to be independent and not as open in this phase.\n Storming. During this phase, the team begins to address the project work, technical decisions, and the project management approach. If team members are not collaborative or open to differing ideas and perspectives, the environment can become counterproductive.\n Norming. In this phase, team members begin to work together and adjust their work habits and behaviors to support the team. The team members learn to trust each other.\n Performing. Teams that reach the performing stage function as a well-organized unit. They are interdependent and work through issues smoothly and effectively.\n Adjourning. In this phase, the team completes the work and moves on from the project. This typically occurs when staff is released from the project as deliverables are completed or as part of the Close Project or Phase process.\n \n The team is Normalising with each other and is in Norming phase. hence the best choice is C.\n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 7. Project Resource Management / 9.4 DEVELOP TEAM, p375', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
