(1348, 1, 2, 1, 'You are the functional lead of your project. Recently, a team member has joined your project and you are impressed with the functional knowledge he possesses. For the past few weeks, you are having multiple conflicts with him over technical decisions that need to be taken. Both of you explain the situation to the project manager and instead of having a dialogue, she decides in favor of the new team member. Which resolution technique did the project manager use?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Force/direct. Pushing ones viewpoint at the expense of others; offering only win-lose solutions, usually enforced through a power position to resolve an emergency. This approach often results to a win-lose situation. In the current situation Project manager has taken decision to take decision in favour of new team member hence Forcing style of conflict resolution works here.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 4. Project Resource Management / 9.5.2.1 INTERPERSONAL AND TEAM SKILLS, p386', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
