(1407, 1, 3, 1, 'You completed all the requirements for the project as per the requirements document. However, the customer is still not happy with the project. Being new to the business, you try to determine the cause so you don\'t lose any future business prospects. Which chart/diagram could be used in this scenario?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Cause-and-effect diagrams. Cause-and-effect diagrams are also known as fishbone diagrams, why-why diagrams, or Ishikawa diagrams. This type of diagram breaks down the causes of the problem statement identified into discrete branches, helping to identify the main or root cause of the problem. \n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 8. Project Quality Management / 8.2.2.4 DATA REPRESENTATION, p330', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
