(1420, 1, 2, 1, 'You accepted your customer\'s request to involve your SME, James, in all important decision-making processes. You worked with your functional manager to acquire James. Which tool did you use to acquire James?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'When physical or team resources for a project are determined in advance, they are considered pre-assigned. This situation can occur if the project is the result of specific resources being identified as part of a competitive proposal or if the project is dependent upon the expertise of particular persons. Pre-assignment might also include the team members who have already been assigned in Develop Project Charter Process or other processes before the initial Resource Management Plan has been completed.\n Since James was preassigned, hence best choice is pre-assignment. \n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 9. Project Resource Management / 9.3.2.3 PRE-ASSIGNMENT, p370', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
