(1423, 1, 3, 1, 'Customer reached out to your team member to implement a cost related change which was initially rejected by the CCB. Your team member told you about it and you contacted the customer to prevent any unapproved changes from being included in the reported cost. Which process are you in?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'Managing Changes is the part of Control cost which is being done by PM here.\n Control Costs is the process of monitoring the status of the project to update the project costs and managing changes to the cost baseline. The key benefit of this process is that the cost baseline is maintained throughout the project. This process is performed throughout the project.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 7. Project Cost Management / 7.4 CONTROL COSTS, p294', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
