(1446, 1, 2, 1, 'You have been asked to handle a project whose PM left the project without a formal handover. The first thing you notice is that the stakeholders are not happy. While determining the root cause, you find out that the project manager made a few decisions without the stakeholders consent. These decisions resulted in the change of the project\'s scope, without going through the integrated change control process. What should your first step be?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'First thing that PM needs to do is to talk to stakholders transparently and explain them the curret state of the the scope of project and once stakeholders agree get the formal cahnge request through CCB. Best choice in current scenario is option C.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
