(1449, 1, 2, 1, 'You have been tasked with creating the project charter for your new project. Who are you?', 1, 1, 'Simple', 'The project charter is the document issued by the project initiator or sponsor that formally authorizes the existence of a project and provides the project manager with the authority to apply organizational resources to project activities. It documents the high-level information on the project and on the product, service, or result the project.\n Sponsor is the person who authorizes the project through Project Charter. Best choice is B.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 4. Project Integration Management / 4.1.3.1 PROJECT CHARTER p118', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
