(1452, 1, 3, 1, 'You are a project manager for a website development project. While analyzing the project network diagram, you determine that there are two paths that share the same duration and they are also the highest duration. You are reviewing high-risk taking activities on these paths. What type of tools and technique did you use?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Since PM is looking at the network diagrams closely and trying to derisk the same. This is part of schedule network analysis. Best choice is B.\n  \n Schedule network analysis is the overarching technique used to generate the project schedule model. It employs several other techniques such as critical path method, resource optimization techniques, and modeling techniques.Additional analysis includes but is not limited to: 1. Assessing the need to aggregate schedule reserves to reduce the probability of a schedule slip when multiple paths converge at a single point in time or when multiple paths diverge from a single point in time, to reduce the probability of a schedule slip. 2.Reviewing the network to see if the critical path has high-risk activities or long lead items that would necessitate\n use of schedule reserves or the implementation of risk responses to reduce the risk on the critical path.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 6 Project Schedule management /6.5.2.1 SCHEDULE NETWORK ANALYSIS, p246', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
