(1455, 1, 3, 1, 'Because of the high risk associated with the project, the sponsor has explicitly montioned that the project should run as smoothly as possible. If the project is not completed within the specified timeline, then the organization will loose million of dollars. Which of the following is not an example of monitor and control project work.', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'Monitor and Control Project Work is the process of tracking, reviewing, and reporting the overall progress to meet the performance objectives defined in the project management plan. The key benefit of this process is that it allows stakeholders to understand the current state of the project, to recognize the actions taken to address any performance issues, and to have visibility into the future project status with cost and schedule forecasts. it doesnot acertain that integrity of baselines will be maintained. Best choice is A.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018), 4. Project Integration Management / 4.5 MONITOR AND CONTROL PROJECT WORK, p142', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
