(1476, 1, 3, 1, 'Ram is a project manager. One of his recent project is scheduled to finish in 1.5 years is running on time However, due to a regulatory requirement, the customer requested him to complete the project in 1 year instead. Based on Ram\'s first reaction, he believes that the request is unachievable. What should Ram do next?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'PM should keep stakeholders informed about the impacts of crashing and then move forward. best choice is option D.\n \n Crashing. A technique used to shorten the schedule duration for the least incremental cost by adding resources. Examples of crashing include approving overtime, bringing in additional resources, or paying to expedite delivery to activities on the critical path. Crashing works only for activities on the critical path where additional resources will shorten the activitys duration.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) PMI/PMBOK 6.5.2.6 SCHEDULE COMPRESSION/ p252', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
