(1508, 1, 1, 1, 'You have been given a responsibility to launch a new product. You decide to launch a prototype in your department first. Based on the positive feedback recoivod, you decide to launch it to a larger target group. Which technique are you using to take a decision?', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'Continual improvement. The plan-do-check-act (PDCA) cycle is the basis for quality improvement as defined by Shewhart and modified by Deming. In addition, quality improvement initiatives such as total quality management (TQM), Six Sigma, and Lean Six Sigma may improve both the quality of project management, as well as the quality of the end product, service, or result.\n \n Best Choice is C.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) PMI/PMI/p312', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
