(1511, 1, 3, 1, 'You are working for the quality control team. Your project in progress and is ready for inspection by the internal quality control team Since you have many projects in the pipeline, you were instructed to reduce the number of quality inspections, which would result in reduction of the project cost. Which technique would be best in this scenario', 1, 1, 'Medium', 'Statistical sampling. Statistical sampling involves choosing part of a population of interest for inspection (for example, selecting 10 engineering drawings at random from a list of 75). The sample is taken to measure controls and verify quality. Sample frequency and sizes should be determined during the Plan Quality Management process.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) PMI/PMI/p340', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
