(1545, 1, 1, 1, 'Shawn is a project manager in a foreign location On his first day, he receives a gift from his vendor The gift is not valuable in his home country but is extremely valuable in the foreign country. Shawn\'s corporate office policy prohibits employees from accepting gifts from vendors. However, since he is new to the location, he is not aware of local customs. What is the best way PM can respond to such a situation?', 1, 1, 'High Complex', 'PM needs to always follow policy as per organisations. If he is not sure, he needs to find out before any actions as implications of not following policy is high as this can be conflict of interest situation. Best choice is C to move forward.', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
