(1551, 1, 3, 1, 'Monty is a new project manager in the vendor management department of the organization. He wants to make sure that none of the bidders receive preferential treatment while bidding for a contract. Which technique should he use to ensure unbiased bidding?', 1, 1, 'Complex', 'Bidder conferences (also called contractor conferences, vendor conferences, and pre-bid conferences) are meetings between the buyer and prospective sellers prior to proposal submittal. They are used to ensure that all prospective bidders have a clear and common understanding of the procurement and no bidders receive preferential treatment.\n \n PM is ensuring that process is fair and it is done in Bidder conferences.\n \n PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition (2018) PMI/PMI/12.2.2.3 BIDDER CONFERENCES/p524', 0, 16, '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
